  "infoProcessTitle": "The Kefir Process",
  "infoProcessStep1Title": "Preparation",
  "infoProcessStep1Desc": "Kefir grains are introduced into milk at room temperature, preferably whole milk (although it can also be semi-skimmed or skimmed).",
  "infoProcessStep2Title": "Fermentation (24h - 48h)",
  "infoProcessStep2Desc": "Microorganisms consume the lactose in the milk, transforming it into lactic acid (which gives its sour taste), carbon dioxide, and other beneficial compounds. The longer it sits, the thicker and more acidic it becomes.",
  "infoProcessStep3Title": "Harvesting",
  "infoProcessStep3Desc": "Strain the mixture with a non-metallic strainer. The resulting liquid is the kefir beverage ready to consume, and the recovered grains are introduced back into fresh milk to repeat the cycle.",
  "infoGuideTitle": "How to use Kefir Control",
  "infoGuideDesc": "This application is designed to help you keep precise track of your fermentation times, preventing your kefir from becoming excessively acidic due to forgetting.",
  "infoGuideStep1Title": "Start Fermentation Now",
  "infoGuideStep1Desc": "Press this button right after mixing the milk with the grains. It will ask you to choose how long you want it to ferment (24, 36, or 48 hours). The app will schedule an automatic alarm.",
  "infoGuideStep2Title": "Record Past Fermentation",
  "infoGuideStep2Desc": "Did you forget to press the button when you prepared the kefir this morning? No problem. Use this option to indicate the exact time (and day) you made the mixture in real life. The app will calculate the elapsed time since then.",
  "infoGuideStep3Title": "Notifications",
  "infoGuideStep3Desc": "You can close the application safely. When the target time is reached, you will receive a notification on your device letting you know it is time to strain the kefir.",
  "infoGuideStep4Title": "Finish Fermentation",
  "infoGuideStep4Desc": "Press this red button once you have strained the kefir to clear the timer and leave the application ready for your next harvest.",
  "infoGuideStepHarvestTitle": "Harvest and Restart",
  "infoGuideStepHarvestDesc": "When you finish a batch, use this new flow to save it and start the next cycle immediately with a single touch.",
  "infoGuideStepAdjustTitle": "Adjust Duration",
  "infoGuideStepAdjustDesc": "Is it warmer than usual? Tap on the progress of any active fermentation to shorten or lengthen its duration.",
